title: Jeb Bush visits Regent University today
text:
Jeb Bush visits Regent University today He will be at Regent University. Staff , 13News Now 7:07 a.m. EDT October 23, 2015 Republican presidential candidate Jeb Bush speaks during the LIBRE Initiative Fourm at the College of Southern Nevada on October 21, 2015 in North Las Vegas, Nevada. (Photo: David Becker, Getty Images) CONNECT TWEET   
VIRGINIA BEACH, Va. (WVEC) -- A presidential hopeful is making a stop in Hampton Roads on Friday. 
Jeb Bush is coming to Regent University, where he will be participating in the school "Presidential Candidates Forum" at 3 p.m. 
The Republican candidate will take part in a live interview, as well as a Q&A session with audience members. He'll be able to discuss his platform in a town-hall style forum. 
Click here for additional information 
Presidential candidates from both parties have been extended invitations to participate in future "Presidential Candidate Forums." 
Jeb Bush, who served as Florida Governor from 1999 to 2007, announced his candidacy on June 15, 2015. He is the son of President George H.W. and First Lady Barbara Bush, and a younger brother of President George W. Bush.  //on.wvec.com/1LRfyiu TOP VIDEOS
